headline: Does Take-Two’s 134.7% Three Year Surge Still Leave Room for Further Returns?
summary: If you are wondering whether Take-Two Interactive Software is still a buy after its huge run, you are not alone. This article will walk through what the current price actually implies about future returns. The stock recently closed at $246.02, up 0.4% over the past week, 5.1% over the last month, and 34.4% year to date, while delivering 29.2% over 1 year and 134.7% over 3 years. headline: Buy Stocks on the Dip? Here’s a Better Strategy.
summary: Many investors welcomed the market’s recent decline as an opportunity to buy the dip. That’s not the best strategy, argue two analysts.
